# Parent uses `with [inner]` to extract the deep child out of `mid`. After
# the instance-graph fix, `parent.inner` and `parent.mid.inner` point at the
# *same* instance, so an overlay applied through `inner` is visible from the
# `mid` side as well — observed indirectly here through `mid`'s own
# parameters that read `value.inner`.
use intermediate as mid [inner]

Direct from inner: direct = value.inner
Forwarded via mid: via_mid = forwarded.mid
Doubled via mid: doubled_mid = doubled.mid
